* the **API build** uses the updated .NET Core template and OWASP parameters, which the current `build-dotnet-core-webapi.yml` already supports 
* the **DB build** uses the current `build-database-project.yml`, which now only builds and publishes the DACPAC, so I removed `previewConnectionString` from the parent pipeline because that parameter is no longer in the template 
* the **release pipeline** becomes environment-driven and validates `release/*` or `hotfix/*` builds instead of `refs/heads/sit`, which matches the newer release pattern you’ve been moving to
* the **DB preview pipeline** follows the same model as your Alterna Telecom preview flow and uses the shared `generate-db-preview.yml` template

